Tap the link in bio for the recipe!

node.text: The inspiration for this Spicy Tofu and Zucchini Stew that @annie.h.shi makes for cozy weeknight dinners every season of the year comes from Soondubu Jjigae, a spicy Korean tofu stew, that she grew up eating at restaurants. The recipe features an umami-rich broth powered by dashi packets, gochugaru, doenjang (fermented soybean paste), and gochujang. Tap the link in bio for the recipe!

Pork shoulder can be transformed into all kinds of delicious meals. Whether you decide to rub it, stuff it, braise it, grill it, chill it, roast it, or marinate it, we got you. Vin d'orange is a potent and easy-to-make fortified wine that smells like an orange grove and tastes of bitter sweetness with an alcoholic bite. Serve it chilled with a single ice cube for a perfect treat. Tap the link in bio for the recipe! 
Recipe🍊: @sjrhoffman @easyandcompany 
📸: @maryjohoffman

node.text: September is the bridge between summer and fall, and in this roundup, we've included dishes for both seasons. If you're still loving sun-ripened produce, make Tomato Soup with Iberico Ham; To celebrate apple season, Pork Chops with Three-Apple Slaw or Apple-Ham Quiche. Tap the link in bio to discover all of the best recipes to try this month. 📸: @protazio
